This engine finally had it. Well,

269
00:20:23,400 --> 00:20:25,900
Iooks like I'll have to take it to Milan.

270
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:33,800
... they were shot down,

271
00:20:34,200 --> 00:20:35,400
but they succeeded in escaping
by parachute.

272
00:20:36,500 --> 00:20:39,800
The air pirates, who took all the money
and gold away from the ship,

273
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:41,500
Ieft the following message,

274
00:20:42,300 --> 00:20:43,500
'You are next, pig!

275
00:20:44,700 --> 00:20:46,500
Come get it, pig!'.

276
00:20:47,700 --> 00:20:49,600
I repeat,

277
00:20:49,900 --> 00:20:50,200
'You are next,pig.

278
00:20:50,700 --> 00:20:51,400
Come get it, pig.'

279
00:20:51,900 --> 00:20:53,200
This crime...

280
00:20:53,800 --> 00:20:55,800
You guys are special kind of trash.

281
00:21:01,400 --> 00:21:03,200
I'm sorry, but I'm going on vacation.

282
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:07,700
White sheets,

283
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:10,700
beautiful ladies...

284
00:21:17,300 --> 00:21:19,900
Don't give out on me yet, Mr. Engine.

285
00:21:44,500 --> 00:21:46,200
I don't like this weather.

286
00:21:46,900 --> 00:21:48,400
Well, guess I'll have
to go under the clouds.

287
00:22:44,600 --> 00:22:45,600
Oh, good boy, hang in there.

288
00:22:50,900 --> 00:22:53,700
Yes, you are a good boy, engine.

289
00:23:05,300 --> 00:23:06,700
Rosso!

290
00:23:15,200 --> 00:23:17,000
Fight me man to man.

291
00:23:17,500 --> 00:23:19,300
I don't have time to play with you.

292
00:23:28,100 --> 00:23:29,000
Don't run away,

293
00:23:29,400 --> 00:23:30,600
or I'm going to tell everybody about it.

294
00:23:31,200 --> 00:23:33,200
See you later, Mr. America, ha ha ha...

295
00:23:36,400 --> 00:23:38,500
Shit, I'm out of the clouds.

296
00:23:41,200 --> 00:23:41,900
Jesus.

297
00:23:43,100 --> 00:23:44,100
Gotcha!

298
00:23:44,600 --> 00:23:46,500
No, you didn't.

299
00:23:46,800 --> 00:23:47,200
It's broken.

300
00:23:58,400 --> 00:23:59,400
I did it!

301
00:23:59,800 --> 00:24:01,200
Now, I'm a celebrity.

302
00:24:19,900 --> 00:24:21,300
They are not going to believe me

303
00:24:21,700 --> 00:24:22,800
if I don't bring back any proof.

304
00:24:23,300 --> 00:24:25,200
Let's see...

305
00:24:31,700 --> 00:24:33,100
Yes!

306
00:24:50,200 --> 00:24:52,600
This cheap, crimson colored piece.
This is it.

307
00:24:54,600 --> 00:24:57,100
This will be a nice gift
for my mom in Alabama.

308
00:25:41,700 --> 00:25:42,800
Please hurry up.

309
00:25:48,400 --> 00:25:49,700
Madam,

310
00:25:51,000 --> 00:25:53,700
madam. Telephone, please.

311
00:25:54,000 --> 00:25:54,800
He is alive after all.

312
00:25:57,300 --> 00:25:58,500
Please get the phone at the front desk.

313
00:26:07,400 --> 00:26:08,400
Marco, is this you?

314
00:26:09,000 --> 00:26:11,300
Did you get hurt?
I was about to leave to pick you up.

315
00:26:12,800 --> 00:26:15,000
Ok, that's fine.

316
00:26:15,500 --> 00:26:18,800
I lost some weight, because I was stranded
on a desert island. I'm going to

317
00:26:19,800 --> 00:26:22,500
Milan to repair my plane.

318
00:26:22,900 --> 00:26:24,900
If that Mr. America stops by your hotel,

319
00:26:26,600 --> 00:26:28,500
tell him this, please,
See you again next time.

320
00:26:29,200 --> 00:26:32,300
What? You think of me as a
bulletin board or something?!

321
00:26:33,000 --> 00:26:35,600
However I'm worried about you guys,
pilots like you regard women

322
00:26:36,000 --> 00:26:38,800
as nails in a landing pier
or something insignificant.

323
00:26:40,700 --> 00:26:44,000
Marco,
you're going to end up as roast pork someday.

324
00:26:44,500 --> 00:26:46,600
I'd hate to witness such a miserable funeral.

325
00:26:48,400 --> 00:26:50,500
A pig who doesn't fly is just an ordinary pig.

326
00:26:50,800 --> 00:26:51,400
Marco, you fool!

327
00:27:46,100 --> 00:27:47,300
Bright red broken wing.

328
00:27:47,700 --> 00:27:49,100
I guess you would come tonight.

329
00:27:49,400 --> 00:27:50,400
I come to disturb you again!

330
00:27:51,000 --> 00:27:55,600
You lost too much this time.
Why don't you just build another one?

331
00:27:56,400 --> 00:27:57,600
I want to keep this one.

332
00:27:58,400 --> 00:27:59,800
I know how you feel.

333
00:28:01,400 --> 00:28:03,400
Step aside, please.
I need drive into the factory.

334
00:28:07,400 --> 00:28:09,300
Who is that cute girl?

335
00:28:09,900 --> 00:28:11,600
My granddaughter,
who was living in America.

336
00:28:14,800 --> 00:28:18,600
Alright, alright, alright.

337
00:28:36,500 --> 00:28:37,600
Nice plane.

338
00:28:38,100 --> 00:28:39,000
It's neat grandpa.

339
00:28:40,000 --> 00:28:41,200
Good design.

340
00:28:41,800 --> 00:28:44,500
There is almost no workers to do the job
like this these days.

341
00:28:45,200 --> 00:28:46,100
She doesn't resemble you.

342
00:28:47,800 --> 00:28:49,200
Is she really your granddaughter?

343
00:28:50,200 --> 00:28:51,100
Don't touch her!

344
00:28:55,400 --> 00:28:56,600
Fio, I leave this to you.

345
00:28:57,600 --> 00:28:58,700
Ok. I'll do it.

346
00:28:59,800 --> 00:29:00,900
The opponent is Curtis.

347
00:29:01,400 --> 00:29:02,800
I need 15 knots more.

348
00:29:03,300 --> 00:29:05,900
Curtis? I've hear of him.

349
00:29:11,500 --> 00:29:12,300
See this.

350
00:29:12,700 --> 00:29:13,900
This is a Hallvolley, isn't it.

351
00:29:14,600 --> 00:29:16,100
Don't ask how I got this.

352
00:29:16,600 --> 00:29:20,600
An ltalian plane
which had this engine lost a race

353
00:29:20,900 --> 00:29:22,000
with Curtis at Schneider's cup in 1927.

354
00:29:22,600 --> 00:29:23,900
But it lost due to poor engineering,

355
00:29:24,300 --> 00:29:26,000
not this engine.

356
00:29:27,800 --> 00:29:29,000
This is exciting.

357
00:29:29,700 --> 00:29:31,500
Don't tune it up too delicately.

358
00:29:32,100 --> 00:29:33,200
My plane is not for such racing.

359
00:29:34,200 --> 00:29:38,100
An Asian proverb calls this Preaching
a sermon to buddha.. Did you know that?

360
00:29:42,600 --> 00:29:44,200
Are you going to take all of my money?

361
00:29:45,300 --> 00:29:49,700
These days,
rolls of bills aren't worth a damn.

362
00:29:50,100 --> 00:29:51,600
Give me money in your pocket,

363
00:29:52,000 --> 00:29:53,900
for propeller and paint and ...

364
00:29:54,000 --> 00:29:57,000
This is for living expenses,
such as hotel and meals.

365
00:29:57,600 --> 00:30:01,000
You can stay here.
I'm not going to charge you much. Meals included.

366
00:30:03,400 --> 00:30:06,200
I don't see your sons.
Are they alright?

367
00:30:06,500 --> 00:30:07,900
All three left looking for works.

368
00:30:08,600 --> 00:30:10,000
Then... who is going to design my plane?

369
00:30:10,700 --> 00:30:11,700
Fio is.

370
00:30:12,200 --> 00:30:14,800
Fio! That's a girl I saw, isn't she.

371
00:30:15,200 --> 00:30:19,600
She is young,
but she's got something my sons lack.

372
00:30:23,700 --> 00:30:25,900
Hey, old man.
We've known each other for long time,

373
00:30:26,600 --> 00:30:28,900
but I'll look
for another repairman this time.

374
00:30:30,900 --> 00:30:31,900
Wait.

375
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:40,000
You are nervous because

376
00:30:40,400 --> 00:30:41,300
I'm a woman, aren't you?
Or, I'm too young to do it?

377
00:30:41,900 --> 00:30:43,400
Both, Miss.

378
00:30:43,800 --> 00:30:45,300
Ok. I agree with you.

379
00:30:48,200 --> 00:30:50,200
Well, can you tell me the first priority
of being a good pilot?

380
00:30:51,900 --> 00:30:52,700
Experience?

381
00:30:53,100 --> 00:30:55,000
No, inspiration, I think.

382
00:30:55,600 --> 00:30:58,100
Oh, I'm glad you didn't say experience.

383
00:30:58,700 --> 00:31:03,200
Anyway, I heard from grandpa
that you flew at an early age.

384
00:31:03,700 --> 00:31:05,800
And have been an excellent pilot since then.

385
00:31:06,800 --> 00:31:09,900
That was 1910, when I was 17.

386
00:31:11,000 --> 00:31:13,300
17! That's the same age I am now.

387
00:31:14,600 --> 00:31:16,600
I can't quit being a woman,

388
00:31:17,000 --> 00:31:18,800
but let me do the job, will you?

389
00:31:19,600 --> 00:31:21,300
If I can't do it well, don't pay me.

390
00:31:22,300 --> 00:31:23,500
Is it ok, grandpa?

391
00:31:23,900 --> 00:31:25,700
She is my granddaughter, she'll do well.

392
00:31:26,400 --> 00:31:29,700
In my case, I was able
to fix engines at the age of 12.

393
00:31:30,300 --> 00:31:32,400
Could you sleep here tonight?
I'll make your bed tomorrow.

394
00:31:32,700 --> 00:31:33,500
The breakfast is at 7:00am.

395
00:31:33,800 --> 00:31:34,500
You can take a hot shower.

396
00:31:34,800 --> 00:31:36,100
I've you left a towel already.
Have a good night.

397
00:31:39,500 --> 00:31:42,300
You don't have enough money.
We know each other well,

398
00:31:42,600 --> 00:31:44,500
so will make the rest a loan.

399
00:32:29,600 --> 00:32:31,600
Good-morning. Did you sleep well?

400
00:32:31,900 --> 00:32:33,000
Did you stay up all night?

401
00:32:33,600 --> 00:32:35,000
This is the rough plan.
What do you think?

402
00:32:35,700 --> 00:32:39,100
I want to redesign this wing section,
leaving the plane shape as it is.

403
00:32:40,200 --> 00:32:42,400
This will make your plane fly faster.

404
00:32:43,400 --> 00:32:45,200
I'm surprised at the original plan.

405
00:32:45,900 --> 00:32:47,800
The wing was also made of wood.

406
00:32:48,600 --> 00:32:50,100
This plane is great.

407
00:32:50,500 --> 00:32:53,600
The designer who designed
this wing must have know the wood very well.

408
00:32:54,700 --> 00:32:55,700
I'm really impressed.

409
00:32:56,500 --> 00:32:58,700
This is the only plane of its kind made,

410
00:32:59,800 --> 00:33:01,500
nobody used it,

411
00:33:02,900 --> 00:33:04,500
just put in the store room.

412
00:33:05,000 --> 00:33:05,900
No wonder!

413
00:33:06,900 --> 00:33:08,400
I'm surprised that this radical design

414
00:33:08,800 --> 00:33:10,200
allows you to take off from water surface.

415
00:33:11,000 --> 00:33:13,300
Only take offs and
landings give me some difficulty.

416
00:33:14,000 --> 00:33:15,900
It behaves strange during the flight.

417
00:33:17,100 --> 00:33:21,100
At 0.5 degrees to the angle
of the wings, right?

418
00:33:21,700 --> 00:33:23,600
Everything should be fine then.

419
00:33:24,000 --> 00:33:25,800
You'll let me continue with this,
won't you?

420
00:33:26,200 --> 00:33:27,300
Thank you, Mr.! I'll do my best!

421
00:33:29,100 --> 00:33:31,600
But let me tell you something, Miss.

422
00:33:33,600 --> 00:33:34,700
Don't stay up all night.

423
00:33:35,100 --> 00:33:36,500
Insomnia prevents
you from doing an excellent job.

424
00:33:37,700 --> 00:33:39,100
And it is not good for your beauty.

425
00:33:40,200 --> 00:33:41,500
Thank you for your advice.

426
00:33:43,100 --> 00:33:44,100
Well,

427
00:33:44,500 --> 00:33:46,600
to be honest,

428
00:33:47,000 --> 00:33:47,900
I couldn't sleep well last night.

429
00:33:48,400 --> 00:33:51,000
I was worried that
you won't let me do this job.

430
00:33:51,500 --> 00:33:52,400
Well, I'm very sleepy now.

431
00:33:52,900 --> 00:33:54,000
I'll make a coffee for you.

432
00:33:56,500 --> 00:33:59,500
Is she going to build this plane alone?

433
00:34:08,600 --> 00:34:09,700
Next is my niece, Monica.
She is will be in charge of general construction.

434
00:34:10,500 --> 00:34:11,000
Nice to meet you.

435
00:34:11,500 --> 00:34:13,400
This is a wife of my nephew, Silvana.

436
00:34:14,000 --> 00:34:14,400
She is going to do finishing construction.

437
00:34:14,800 --> 00:34:15,200
These are daughters of my relatives.

438
00:34:15,500 --> 00:34:18,000
Sophia, Laura, Constance, Valentina.

439
00:34:18,400 --> 00:34:20,000
This is Fio's elder sister, Giliora.

440
00:34:20,300 --> 00:34:22,300
Oh, you're looking for me?
This is Sandra, my cousin.

441
00:34:22,400 --> 00:34:23,500
You look so pretty Marietta.

442
00:34:24,200 --> 00:34:25,300
Wives of my sons,

443
00:34:25,700 --> 00:34:26,400
Maria,

444
00:34:26,700 --> 00:34:29,000
Tina, Anna, and her younger sister Birreta.

445
00:34:29,800 --> 00:34:30,900
Angelino!

446
00:34:31,300 --> 00:34:32,400
Grandma!

447
00:34:33,600 --> 00:34:35,300
Are you still alive?

448
00:34:37,400 --> 00:34:39,800
You've grown up to be a nice boy!

449
00:34:43,100 --> 00:34:44,800
Are you ladies going to work?

450
00:34:46,300 --> 00:34:49,100
Yes, I'd like to have some money
for my great-grandchildren.

451
00:34:54,500 --> 00:34:56,300
There are no man here, right?

452
00:34:58,400 --> 00:34:59,800
Ah...

453
00:35:00,200 --> 00:35:01,000
All these are your relatives?

454
00:35:01,400 --> 00:35:02,600
Yes, they don't have any jobs these days.

455
00:35:03,200 --> 00:35:05,000
All the men went to other places to work.

456
00:35:07,400 --> 00:35:08,900
Because of the 'Great Depression'?

457
00:35:09,800 --> 00:35:10,900
Don't worry.

458
00:35:11,300 --> 00:35:12,100
Girls are nice,

459
00:35:12,400 --> 00:35:13,300
they work very well and are also gutsy.

460
00:35:13,700 --> 00:35:17,600
Making an airplane is in no way
like baking a cake, I think...

461
00:35:26,000 --> 00:35:28,000
Dear God.

462
00:35:28,600 --> 00:35:30,500
You gave my company,
which was about to go bankrupt,

463
00:35:30,900 --> 00:35:32,500
a piece of bread and a job.

464
00:35:33,100 --> 00:35:37,500
Please forgive us,
who make a fighter plane with ladies.

465
00:35:37,800 --> 00:35:39,000
Amen.

466
00:35:41,900 --> 00:35:44,600
Well, let's eat well and work hard!

467
00:35:55,100 --> 00:35:58,100
Sounds good!
This engine is quite something!

468
00:36:05,500 --> 00:36:07,300
What do you say, it's nice, isn't it?

469
00:36:07,900 --> 00:36:10,900
Don't over do it
or this factory will be gone.

470
00:36:13,000 --> 00:36:15,400
Huh, you think Curtis is not worth it?

471
00:36:47,000 --> 00:36:48,100
Uh-hm, sure, this is a good idea.

472
00:36:49,400 --> 00:36:51,300
So, let me do it.

473
00:36:52,100 --> 00:36:54,600
But, this is going to cost a fortune.

474
00:36:55,400 --> 00:36:58,700
I got a lot of bills already.

475
00:36:59,600 --> 00:37:01,500
I'm not sure what sponsor thinks.

476
00:37:03,300 --> 00:37:04,500
Porco...

477
00:37:06,800 --> 00:37:09,100
Ok, ok. Don't look at me like that.

478
00:37:10,000 --> 00:37:10,900
Do it your way.

479
00:37:11,500 --> 00:37:13,500
Yes! I've already talked to manufacturers.

480
00:37:14,000 --> 00:37:14,800
I will order these immediately.

481
00:37:15,500 --> 00:37:16,900
Porco, I love you!

482
00:37:21,400 --> 00:37:23,000
Wait at least three months, will you?

483
00:37:23,700 --> 00:37:25,600
I want to change my job
and become an air pirate.

484
00:37:26,400 --> 00:37:27,600
She is a nice girl, isn't she.

485
00:37:28,500 --> 00:37:29,700
Don't touch her.

486
00:37:30,400 --> 00:37:32,700
If I would be henpecked,
I could not feel happy.

487
00:38:47,600 --> 00:38:49,700
You're a major, ah.
You rose in the world, Fierrali.

488
00:38:50,200 --> 00:38:51,700
You, fool. Why did you come back?

489
00:38:52,900 --> 00:38:54,800
I make it a rule to go wherever I want to.

490
00:38:55,700 --> 00:38:57,500
The government is not going
to let you go this time.

491
00:38:58,600 --> 00:38:59,800
Did somebody follow you?

492
00:39:00,200 --> 00:39:01,200
I gave them the slip.

493
00:39:01,900 --> 00:39:11,100
A warrant for your arrest
is going to be issued.

494
00:39:12,800 --> 00:39:14,200
Hey, this is no time to laugh.

495
00:39:15,700 --> 00:39:18,400
They say they will confiscate your plane.

496
00:39:19,500 --> 00:39:21,500
This movie is crap, don't you think.

497
00:39:22,400 --> 00:39:24,300
Hey, Marco, come back to the air force.

498
00:39:24,800 --> 00:39:27,300
I would make a room for you.

499
00:39:28,000 --> 00:39:30,300
I'd rather be a pig then a fascist.

500
00:39:30,800 --> 00:39:32,800
The era of sky adventures has gone.

501
00:39:33,200 --> 00:39:36,600
The only thing left for us to do is

502
00:39:38,500 --> 00:39:41,200
to fly for such ridiculous reasons
as the country or the nation.

503
00:39:42,600 --> 00:39:45,000
You are a pig after all, huh?

504
00:39:45,900 --> 00:39:49,300
Thanks for your advice, Fierrali.
Give my regards to the others.

505
00:39:50,900 --> 00:39:53,700
This is a nice film, don't you think.
Watch your tail cowboy.

506
00:39:54,200 --> 00:39:56,500
They don't sue a pigs, but...

507
00:39:58,500 --> 00:40:00,300
Goodbye, my comrade.

508
00:40:18,800 --> 00:40:19,900
Porco, need a ride?

509
00:40:25,300 --> 00:40:26,700
Hey, you're a life saver.

510
00:40:33,200 --> 00:40:35,600
I borrowed this because
I need to take your plane to the lake tomorrow.

511
00:40:36,500 --> 00:40:37,800
It's for a test flight, right?

512
00:40:38,500 --> 00:40:40,900
I don't need the test flight.
I need to fly as soon as possible.

513
00:40:42,200 --> 00:40:43,200
Don't be such a fool.

514
00:40:43,600 --> 00:40:45,400
I'm not going to give you the plane
without testing it.

515
00:40:46,200 --> 00:40:49,400
Besides, it will take almost a day
to take it apart and transport it to the lake.

516
00:40:49,700 --> 00:40:50,700
We don't have much time.

517
00:40:51,200 --> 00:40:52,800
Take a look back, will you, slowly.

518
00:40:53,600 --> 00:40:57,900
That's the fascists secret police.

519
00:40:59,500 --> 00:41:00,700
They were following you, Fio.

520
00:41:01,600 --> 00:41:03,600
Me? Why? For what?

521
00:41:04,400 --> 00:41:06,000
Because I gave them the slip.

522
00:41:06,600 --> 00:41:09,300
And, because you are working on my plane.

523
00:41:13,500 --> 00:41:15,400
Porco, are you really a spy?

524
00:41:20,000 --> 00:41:21,900
Ha, ha, ha, ha! l? A spy?
Ha, ha, ha, ha.

525
00:41:23,500 --> 00:41:27,200
Look, a secret agent works much harder then l.

526
00:41:27,600 --> 00:41:29,900
But, you were a hero at the time of war.

527
00:41:30,800 --> 00:41:33,100
This is strange if you didn't do anything...

