Miss Fio! See you soon!

793
01:02:41,900 --> 01:02:43,000
This sucks!

794
01:02:43,500 --> 01:02:46,000
Hey pig, don't run away!

795
01:02:46,400 --> 01:02:49,500
Shut up, get lost!

796
01:02:50,600 --> 01:02:52,400
Bye-bye!

797
01:02:55,400 --> 01:03:00,000
This is ridiculous. Well, you are.....

798
01:03:00,300 --> 01:03:04,500
Don't tell me. I know, I am foolish.

799
01:03:11,100 --> 01:03:12,000
Fio,

800
01:03:12,700 --> 01:03:15,700
I think I have to say thank you.

801
01:03:16,500 --> 01:03:18,100
You gave me a chance to fight Curtis.

802
01:03:18,800 --> 01:03:19,800
Thanks.

803
01:03:20,400 --> 01:03:22,400
We share the same luck.

804
01:03:23,300 --> 01:03:24,600
We are partners, aren't we?

805
01:03:26,700 --> 01:03:28,400
We are going to have a hard time.

806
01:03:30,000 --> 01:03:31,300
I trust you.

807
01:03:33,200 --> 01:03:36,300
Trust me, eh?
I haven't heard that in a long time,

808
01:03:36,700 --> 01:03:38,300
but I'm glad you said that.

809
01:03:44,300 --> 01:03:46,700
What's wrong? You feel sick?

810
01:03:47,700 --> 01:03:48,300
Fio?

811
01:03:48,800 --> 01:03:49,800
I'm fine.

812
01:03:50,900 --> 01:03:54,000
It's just that my heart is pounding.

813
01:03:54,800 --> 01:04:00,000
To be honest, I was really scared.

814
01:04:03,900 --> 01:04:05,400
Hey?

815
01:04:05,700 --> 01:04:06,900
I want to swim.

816
01:04:25,900 --> 01:04:27,500
Porco! I made a mistake!

817
01:04:28,100 --> 01:04:29,100
Are you O.K?

818
01:04:30,000 --> 01:04:32,700
I should have padded the deal.

819
01:04:33,900 --> 01:04:35,600
We have a bad bargain.

820
01:04:39,300 --> 01:04:41,400
HA,HA,HA,HA.
You're right. HA,HA,HA,HA.

821
01:05:34,800 --> 01:05:36,100
Porco....

822
01:05:36,200 --> 01:05:36,600
Hmm?

823
01:05:37,800 --> 01:05:38,700
You can't sleep, can you?

824
01:05:40,400 --> 01:05:44,500
Now, I just saw...
It may have been a dream...

825
01:05:46,200 --> 01:05:47,400
Every thing is all right.

826
01:05:47,900 --> 01:05:49,200
It's too early in the morning to get up.

827
01:05:50,600 --> 01:05:51,800
Porco.

828
01:05:52,300 --> 01:05:54,300
Why did you become a pig?

829
01:05:55,000 --> 01:05:56,600
I don't know.

830
01:05:57,900 --> 01:06:01,200
I know a lot about Captain Marco Pabatto.

831
01:06:01,600 --> 01:06:03,900
My father used to be in the same unit.

832
01:06:04,300 --> 01:06:06,400
I've heard many a story,
in which the captain

833
01:06:06,800 --> 01:06:10,800
saved lives of enemy pilots,
I liked it.

834
01:06:15,700 --> 01:06:17,600
Porco! How about if I kiss you?

835
01:06:19,500 --> 01:06:23,000
You know a fairy tale
where a princess takes off

836
01:06:23,400 --> 01:06:24,900
a curse on a prince,
who was changed to a frog.

837
01:06:25,300 --> 01:06:28,800
You, silly. Save it for your man!

838
01:06:30,900 --> 01:06:32,600
Won't my kiss work?

839
01:06:35,200 --> 01:06:36,800
Huh, you are a nice girl.

840
01:06:37,300 --> 01:06:38,600
You make me feel comfortable

841
01:06:39,000 --> 01:06:41,700
and make me wish
to be a human being again.

842
01:06:42,700 --> 01:06:44,500
Be a nice girl and go to sleep.

843
01:06:44,800 --> 01:06:46,900
Tell me your story and I will.

844
01:06:48,700 --> 01:06:49,900
My story?

845
01:06:52,300 --> 01:06:53,400
Well...

846
01:07:02,300 --> 01:07:05,500
It was the last summer of the war.

847
01:07:06,300 --> 01:07:12,300
We were fly over the Adriatic Sea
on our usual patrol.

848
01:07:17,700 --> 01:07:20,500
Belneldi was flying on my right side.

849
01:07:21,000 --> 01:07:24,800
He was an old friend of mine.
He got married just two days before.

850
01:07:26,600 --> 01:07:29,600
I was the matchmaker.

851
01:07:30,200 --> 01:07:31,700
He didn't have enough leave
to be with his wife for long.

852
01:07:32,100 --> 01:07:34,500
So, he returned to duty.

853
01:07:54,800 --> 01:07:57,900
Everyone was falling down like flies,
whether a friend or a foe.

854
01:07:58,700 --> 01:08:01,000
I was chased by three planes,

855
01:08:02,000 --> 01:08:04,100
and had no time to worry about my friend.

856
01:08:04,800 --> 01:08:07,400
At the end I was the only one
remaining of my unit.

857
01:08:07,900 --> 01:08:10,000
But, they never gave up chasing me.

858
01:08:10,600 --> 01:08:12,200
I made desperate efforts to run away.

859
01:08:13,000 --> 01:08:14,600
My hands and feet went numb,

860
01:08:15,000 --> 01:08:18,100
and I grew dizzy.
I thought I was going to die.

861
01:08:18,600 --> 01:08:19,800
It was at that time that

862
01:08:20,300 --> 01:08:22,500
I saw the white sky.

863
01:08:23,000 --> 01:08:24,100
White?

864
01:08:25,100 --> 01:08:26,900
Yeah, it was like a flash.

865
01:08:28,900 --> 01:08:33,100
Because of the brightness,
it took me a while to realize that I was in a cloud.

866
01:08:34,100 --> 01:08:37,800
I was worn out, and
didn't have any power left to control my plane.

867
01:08:38,800 --> 01:08:41,700
In spite of that my plane continued to fly.

868
01:09:08,400 --> 01:09:10,100
A cloud of planes...

869
01:09:12,000 --> 01:09:13,400
Yeah, it was calm,

870
01:09:13,900 --> 01:09:15,700
and the sky was very clear, too clear.

871
01:09:16,600 --> 01:09:21,700
There was a line of clouds far above me.

872
01:09:49,200 --> 01:09:51,100
Belneldi, you are alive, aren't you!

873
01:09:55,100 --> 01:09:57,200
Belneldi, wait, where are you going!

874
01:10:10,500 --> 01:10:13,500
Belneldi, don't go!
Are you going to leave Gina alone?!

875
01:10:14,500 --> 01:10:15,800
I'll go instead of you!

876
01:10:56,200 --> 01:11:00,900
When I recovered my senses, I was flying
over the sea, almost touching it, alone.

877
01:11:04,700 --> 01:11:07,200
God said it wasn't your time yet,
didn't he?

878
01:11:09,500 --> 01:11:14,000
In my mind I thought he might
let me fly like that forever.

879
01:11:14,400 --> 01:11:16,400
That would not have been right,
because your are a good guy!

880
01:11:17,400 --> 01:11:19,900
Good guys are all dead already.

881
01:11:20,500 --> 01:11:22,400
Besides, there might have been
Hell inside that cloud.

882
01:11:23,100 --> 01:11:26,100
Well, my story is over.
Go to sleep.

883
01:11:28,600 --> 01:11:31,400
Shit, they gave me crap...

884
01:11:33,500 --> 01:11:36,100
I'm glad you came back to live

885
01:11:36,600 --> 01:11:38,400
because I like you.

886
01:11:40,200 --> 01:11:41,100
Good-night!

887
01:12:05,300 --> 01:12:06,500
Hey, hey, which one's gonna win,
a pig or...

888
01:12:06,800 --> 01:12:08,600
08:07

889
01:12:12,400 --> 01:12:14,400
you need ice-cream, telescope?

890
01:12:23,200 --> 01:12:25,900
Fools. They make our fight into a festival.

891
01:12:26,400 --> 01:12:28,000
Are they all air pirates?

892
01:12:28,500 --> 01:12:30,000
Trash of the Mediterranean Sea...

893
01:12:30,600 --> 01:12:36,400
Gangs, pirates, smugglers,
spies and even some ordinary people.

894
01:12:38,000 --> 01:12:40,400
Heh, this makes my fame rise more and more...

895
01:12:41,700 --> 01:12:44,600
Ten minutes till start,
ten minutes till start!

896
01:12:45,900 --> 01:12:50,400
This is the fight between Porco Rosso
and Donald Curtis!

897
01:12:51,200 --> 01:12:52,600
There are no special rules,

898
01:12:53,000 --> 01:12:56,900
but an unfair fight will a
disgrace to their fans.

899
01:12:57,800 --> 01:12:59,400
Shut up and start right now. Back off!

900
01:13:04,700 --> 01:13:08,500
You shut up, or I kill you!

901
01:13:17,800 --> 01:13:19,800
He'd be better off throwing a 10ton bomb...

902
01:13:20,500 --> 01:13:24,600
This is the fight which will determine
the future of Miss Fio Piccolo.

903
01:13:25,100 --> 01:13:26,600
Shut up!

904
01:13:27,500 --> 01:13:28,500
Do you understand?

905
01:13:28,900 --> 01:13:30,200
If you do, clap your hands.

906
01:13:30,600 --> 01:13:31,400
CLAP!

907
01:13:35,600 --> 01:13:43,300
Shut up, that's the routine.
Well, both of you present your bids.

908
01:13:47,600 --> 01:13:48,300
Have a seat.

909
01:13:48,600 --> 01:13:49,300
Thank you.

910
01:13:50,300 --> 01:13:51,800
Put it on the chair properly!

911
01:13:54,700 --> 01:13:58,500
None of you have anything to say, do you.
Well shake hands or something before you start!

912
01:13:59,200 --> 01:14:02,000
No way. I'm fond of cleanliness.

913
01:14:04,400 --> 01:14:07,000
He's hard to please.

914
01:14:07,300 --> 01:14:09,500
Fio, as soon as this fight is over,
we will go to the church.

915
01:14:11,200 --> 01:14:14,900
Don't worry.
My mom told me your going to like me soon.

916
01:14:20,300 --> 01:14:21,000
You...

917
01:14:21,300 --> 01:14:22,800
May I take a picture with you?

918
01:14:23,100 --> 01:14:24,000
I took a shower already.

919
01:14:24,400 --> 01:14:25,800
Everybody, smile!

920
01:14:26,400 --> 01:14:28,200
SMILE!

921
01:14:49,500 --> 01:14:52,300
If the flight is over in 3 minutes,
the black plane has the advantage...

922
01:14:53,100 --> 01:14:56,600
This is great.
I want them to do this event every month

923
01:14:59,400 --> 01:15:01,400
15 seconds to go.

924
01:15:05,700 --> 01:15:06,800
They are so cool...

925
01:15:08,800 --> 01:15:09,700
5 seconds to go.

926
01:15:10,300 --> 01:15:14,500
4 , 3, 2, 1, 0!

927
01:15:23,100 --> 01:15:24,400
Curtis took over!

928
01:15:42,600 --> 01:15:44,400
This is going to be a one-sided fight.

929
01:15:44,800 --> 01:15:45,800
Give me that.

930
01:15:52,300 --> 01:15:54,700
Porco, what are you doing! Fly over!

931
01:15:55,100 --> 01:15:57,100
He would be shot if the took off now.

932
01:15:57,600 --> 01:15:59,600
It's very difficult for Curtis
to shoot Porco in this situation.

933
01:16:06,300 --> 01:16:08,800
I know you want me to waste the bullet's.
I know it.

934
01:16:25,100 --> 01:16:27,300
Looping! The pig took Curtis' back!

935
01:16:28,100 --> 01:16:29,100
Looping?

936
01:16:29,600 --> 01:16:31,900
His skill made the pig
an ace of the Adriatic Sea.

937
01:16:37,400 --> 01:16:38,200
Shit!

938
01:16:44,500 --> 01:16:45,400
He's gonna shoot!

939
01:16:50,300 --> 01:16:51,200
He doesn't open fire.

940
01:16:51,600 --> 01:16:52,600
Is his machine-gun broken!?

941
01:16:53,100 --> 01:16:54,300
I got it, I got it!

942
01:16:55,000 --> 01:16:56,800
The pig won't shoot until the end.

943
01:16:58,000 --> 01:16:59,300
The pig doesn't kill anybody.

944
01:17:00,300 --> 01:17:02,300
Now, the American should be fine.

945
01:17:02,900 --> 01:17:04,000
You got it! Go and shoot!

946
01:17:04,800 --> 01:17:07,800
Oh, he didn't shoot yet.... See,
I told you...

947
01:17:08,700 --> 01:17:10,900
If the pig opened fire,
it would kill the American, so, it's going to hit

948
01:17:11,500 --> 01:17:15,400
Curtis' engine a few bullets
after Curtis gets tired.

949
01:17:16,200 --> 01:17:19,100
He said this is not war, but...

950
01:17:19,600 --> 01:17:20,400
Porco...

951
01:17:21,600 --> 01:17:23,000
Are you teasing me or what?

952
01:17:23,500 --> 01:17:24,400
Come on!

953
01:17:25,800 --> 01:17:30,300
Is your gun broken, huh! You,
poor bastard!

954
01:17:35,600 --> 01:17:37,000
They are coming this way!

955
01:17:40,100 --> 01:17:42,500
Come on, pig!

956
01:17:47,600 --> 01:17:48,600
Go away from here and fight over there!

957
01:17:50,200 --> 01:17:51,400
Great! The pig is leaving a cloud trail.

958
01:17:53,200 --> 01:17:54,500
Come on!

959
01:18:04,600 --> 01:18:06,300
Shoot that side!

960
01:18:11,300 --> 01:18:13,900
It's cool! It's the first time
I saw the plance leaving a cloud trail!

961
01:18:20,200 --> 01:18:23,800
I've never seen such an air fight before.

962
01:18:24,100 --> 01:18:25,400
I'm really impressed.

963
01:18:34,300 --> 01:18:36,400
I ready for the flight.

964
01:18:36,800 --> 01:18:38,000
She'd better hurry,
or the fight will be over.

965
01:18:38,600 --> 01:18:40,600
She's in her room, and doesn't come out.

966
01:18:41,300 --> 01:18:43,400
Does she want to go or not?

967
01:18:43,800 --> 01:18:45,200
I want to see that fight...

968
01:18:56,300 --> 01:18:59,200
To G of Heart, for the pig.

969
01:18:59,700 --> 01:19:02,600
The air force found out about the fight.
Stop the silly fight.

970
01:19:03,000 --> 01:19:04,800
Oh, this is must be from Fierrali.

971
01:19:08,100 --> 01:19:09,300
I should hurry.

972
01:19:28,200 --> 01:19:30,600
First of all,
both of them are very tough.

973
01:19:31,300 --> 01:19:33,000
The show isn't over!

974
01:19:35,700 --> 01:19:37,600
Porco, fight!

975
01:19:42,600 --> 01:19:43,800
I'm not going to give Fio to a man

976
01:19:49,600 --> 01:19:51,900
Iike you.

977
01:19:58,500 --> 01:19:59,600
O.K. The pig took Curtis' tail.

978
01:20:00,400 --> 01:20:01,600
It's over!

979
01:20:14,200 --> 01:20:16,000
This is the finish.

980
01:20:18,200 --> 01:20:22,000
Whoops... Jammed, too.

981
01:20:22,900 --> 01:20:25,900
You, idiot! You are out of ammo!

982
01:20:26,800 --> 01:20:29,600
Whoops.
This is broken because of Fio's butt...

983
01:20:32,600 --> 01:20:35,000
I'm not going to finish this fight with a draw.

984
01:20:37,200 --> 01:20:40,300
Ha, ha, ha, ha.
This is not a western. You can't hit me.

985
01:20:42,900 --> 01:20:44,900
You...

986
01:20:46,500 --> 01:20:50,700
You really think it will reach here?

987
01:20:58,500 --> 01:20:59,900
You, stinking pig!

988
01:21:02,800 --> 01:21:04,100
Can't throw it!

989
01:21:05,600 --> 01:21:06,400
Bastard!

990
01:21:06,900 --> 01:21:07,500
Throw it finally!

991
01:21:08,000 --> 01:21:08,900
For love!

992
01:21:09,200 --> 01:21:10,200
Shut up! You piggy!

993
01:21:11,500 --> 01:21:12,600
Looks like something is wrong.

994
01:21:13,700 --> 01:21:14,800
Ah... they are coming.

995
01:21:23,400 --> 01:21:24,300
They are coming back!

996
01:21:24,800 --> 01:21:27,300
Wait! Bids don't leave from here.

997
01:21:28,600 --> 01:21:30,200
O.K. Wait, you guys.

998
01:21:37,400 --> 01:21:38,600
You, fat pig!

999
01:21:40,800 --> 01:21:42,100
You, chicken cowboy!

1000
01:21:48,700 --> 01:21:50,200
Come on with your bare hands!

1001
01:21:50,500 --> 01:21:51,700
Go back to cows!

1002
01:21:57,800 --> 01:22:00,600
Porco, hold on!

1003
01:22:02,800 --> 01:22:04,000
Stand up, pig.

1004
01:22:08,500 --> 01:22:10,100
Go, go!

1005
01:22:37,800 --> 01:22:42,900
Bets still stand!

1006
01:22:43,200 --> 01:22:45,900
Where's the betting table?

1007
01:22:49,800 --> 01:22:50,600
Can't you fly faster, much faster?

1008
01:22:51,100 --> 01:22:53,500
It's impossible. Engine would blow.

1009
01:22:54,300 --> 01:22:56,200
Pilots are all stupid, aren't they...

1010
01:23:02,900 --> 01:23:07,100
Hey, Fio. Did you see my punch?

1011
01:23:10,600 --> 01:23:13,100
I'm gonna take him down next round.

1012
01:23:13,800 --> 01:23:16,100
I'll take you down this time.

1013
01:23:16,300 --> 01:23:17,800
Porco, hang on!

1014
01:23:18,500 --> 01:23:21,400
I'll make prosciutto out of you!

1015
01:23:22,700 --> 01:23:23,900
Take aim!

1016
01:23:25,400 --> 01:23:26,800
Come on, you chicken!

1017
01:23:27,500 --> 01:23:28,800
You are the chicken!

1018
01:23:29,400 --> 01:23:31,200
You seduce all women around you.

1019
01:23:31,500 --> 01:23:32,800
That was my word.

1020
01:23:33,300 --> 01:23:35,000
Choose Gina or Fio, either one!

1021
01:23:35,600 --> 01:23:36,800
What?

1022
01:23:40,000 --> 01:23:42,400
Don't choose both.

1023
01:23:44,300 --> 01:23:45,900
Gina is...

1024
01:23:47,900 --> 01:23:51,100
Don't say, Gina, Gina...

1025
01:23:52,200 --> 01:23:56,500
Gina loves you, pig.

1026
01:23:59,800 --> 01:24:01,800
She is...

1027
01:24:02,500 --> 01:24:05,900
waiting for you...

1028
01:24:06,300 --> 01:24:10,800
at the garden!

1029
01:24:18,700 --> 01:24:19,700
Porco!

1030
01:24:20,100 --> 01:24:21,900
The sound of drum.

1031
01:24:23,700 --> 01:24:26,300
It's over! Look at that!

1032
01:24:30,400 --> 01:24:32,700
I can see it.
The ltalian Air Force hasn't arrived, yet.

1033
01:24:44,300 --> 01:24:47,300
You are unfair... You're a dirty liar.

1034
01:24:51,500 --> 01:24:54,300
Don't you understand, you idiot.

1035
01:24:54,700 --> 01:24:56,500
I am not telling a lie...

1036
01:24:59,700 --> 01:25:02,200
I don't give Fio to you.

1037
01:25:02,800 --> 01:25:04,500
That's Gina's plane.

1038
01:25:06,700 --> 01:25:08,200
It's an emergency signal.

1039
01:25:20,100 --> 01:25:22,400
1, 2...

1040
01:25:22,600 --> 01:25:24,300
The winner is the one who stand up first.

1041
01:25:25,600 --> 01:25:27,300
Everybody, let me through.

1042
01:25:27,800 --> 01:25:31,800
6, 7, Gina, don't.

1043
01:25:33,400 --> 01:25:34,100
8!

1044
01:25:36,000 --> 01:25:37,900
Marco, Marco, can you hear me?

1045
01:25:41,100 --> 01:25:43,700
Do you want another girl to be unhappy?

1046
01:25:49,200 --> 01:25:50,300
9!

1047
01:25:53,200 --> 01:25:54,300
Porco!

1048
01:25:57,400 --> 01:25:58,500
Porco!

1049
01:25:58,800 --> 01:26:00,300
Porco, thank you!

1050
01:26:01,000 --> 01:26:02,700
Well...

1051
01:26:10,100 --> 01:26:11,400
This party is over.

1052
01:26:11,800 --> 01:26:13,500
The Air Force will be here soon.

1053
01:26:14,400 --> 01:26:15,700
Everybody run away quickly, please.

1054
01:26:16,900 --> 01:26:20,800
Then stop by my restaurant.
I will serve you all.

